quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  16,66,"And there is a lesson for you in cattle: We give you a drink from their bellies, from between waste and blood, pure milk, refreshing to the drinkers"
  16,67,"And from the fruits of date-palms and grapevines, you derive sugar and wholesome food. In this is a sign for people who understand"
  16,68,"And your Lord inspired the bee: 'Set up hives in the mountains, and in the trees, and in what they construct"
  16,69,"Then eat of all the fruits, and go along the pathways of your Lord, with precision. From their bellies emerges a fluid of diverse colors, containing healing for the people. Surely in this is a sign for people who reflect"
  16,70,"God created you; then He takes you away. Some of you will be brought back to the worst age, so that he will no longer know anything, after having acquired knowledge. God is Omniscient and Omnipotent"